& [SLMLexicalAuthorityFoundationContract] is the contract for the first-class SLM lexical substrate under diffusion
  + [contract_uuid] is a83848bd-2263-43c9-b252-05e27c5b3854
  + [slice_id] is SLM-13
  + [depends_on] is SLM_Core_Data_Contracts, SLM_Evidence_Workspace_Contract, SLM_LLM_Provider_Adapter_Contract
  + [status] is implemented_v0

  & [LexicalSubstrateLayer] is the foundational word-type evidence provider inside SLM's runtime body
    + [purpose] is provide speed-dial lexical and grammatical evidence before diffusion
    + [authority_artifact] is slm_lexicon/data/slm_lexicon.sqlite
    + [runtime_artifact] is slm_lexicon/data/slm_lexical_substrate/term_role_sense_index.json
    + [runtime_manifest] is slm_lexicon/data/slm_lexical_substrate/manifest.json
    + [runtime_manifest_sop] is slm_lexicon/data/slm_lexical_substrate/manifest.sop
    + [closed_class_speed_table] is slm_lexicon/data/slm_lexical_substrate/closed_class_speed_table.json
    + [closed_class_source] is slm_lexicon/seeds/closed_class_terms.json
    + [open_class_source] is Open English WordNet 2025 XML
    + [runtime_provider] is slm_rust/src/lexicon.rs LexicalSubstrateProvider
    + [output] is GrammarCandidate evidence through ProviderSuggestion records
    - never: promote lexical rows directly into SemanticGraph
    - never: treat dictionary membership as semantic truth

  & [ClosedClassLexicon] is the project-owned structural word authority
    + [covers] is articles
    + [covers] is determiners
    + [covers] is prepositions
    + [covers] is conjunctions
    + [covers] is auxiliaries
    + [covers] is modals
    + [covers] is negators
    + [covers] is quantifiers
    + [field] is diffusion_priority
    + [field] is structural_hint
    = must: be checked early because function words constrain relation and scope
    = must: preserve ambiguous closed-class roles when present

  & [OpenClassLexicon] is the imported WordNet-backed semantic evidence source
    + [covers] is nouns
    + [covers] is verbs
    + [covers] is adjectives
    + [covers] is adverbs
    + [field] is sense_key
    + [field] is synset_id
    + [field] is definition
    + [field] is relation_type for synset relations
    = must: remain source-attributed to Open English WordNet
    = must: provide possible roles and senses without collapsing them

  & [SubstrateBuildPath] is the rebuildable local digestion pipeline
    + [step] is python slm_lexicon/scripts/download_open_english_wordnet.py
    + [step] is python slm_lexicon/scripts/build_lexicon_db.py
    + [step] is python slm_lexicon/scripts/build_lexical_substrate_pack.py
    + [generated] is SQLite authority database
    + [generated] is first-class lexical substrate pack
    + [legacy_debug_artifact] is optional JSON lookup cache from export_lexicon_cache.py
    = must: keep generated data outside source-control intent unless explicitly vendored later

  & [EvidenceBoundary] is the protection against premature semantics
    = must: lexical authority creates evidence only
    = must: lexical grammar roles enter EvidenceWorkspace as LexicalAuthority source records
    = must: diffusion may use closed-class priority as structural pressure
    = must: stabilization still requires faculty convergence
    - never: allow WordNet synset identity to become a Glyph without deliberative stabilization

  & [RuntimePolicyDecision] is accepted for v0
    + [decision] is Rust runtime reads generated lexical substrate pack rather than SQLite directly
    + [reason] is Windows Application Control blocked native SQLite Rust build scripts
    + [preserved_authority] is SQLite remains the inspectable generated database
    + [preserved_runtime] is lexical substrate pack is generated from SQLite and source-attributed

  ! [Slice13Complete] is accepted
    @ [support] local database and cache were generated from closed-class seed plus Open English WordNet
    @ [support] Rust LexicalSubstrateProvider maps substrate rows into lexical authority grammar evidence
